FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,FThe Prime Minister has been accused of
OL,7,Fmisleading MPs by saying "full due
OL,8,Fprocess" was followed in appointing
OL,9,FLord Mandelson, who was given
OL,10,Fdeveloped vetting status despite
OL,11,Ffailing security checks.
OL,13,FThe Foreign Office, under then top
OL,14,Fcivil servant Sir Olly, cleared him
OL,15,Fdespite red flags raised by experts at
OL,16,Fthe UK Security Vetting (UKSV) agency.
OL,26,@oD@ZOUpD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,FMr Collard, who briefed Sir Olly on
OL,7,Fthe vetting findings, also did not see
OL,8,Fthe UKSV file recommending clearance
OL,9,Fbe denied, according to the letter
OL,10,Fpublished on Monday.
OL,12,FInstead, he received an oral briefing
OL,13,Ffrom officials which led him to
OL,14,Fbelieve Lord Mandelson's case was
OL,15,F"borderline" and that "the risks could
OL,16,Fbe mitigated," the evidence said.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@LO]wD@WOUxD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,FShe said: "The Prime Minister misled
OL,7,Fthe House of Commons repeatedly. He
OL,8,Fappointed a national security risk and
OL,9,Ffriend of a convicted paedophile to be
OL,10,Four ambassador in Washington, our most
OL,11,Fsensitive diplomatic post"
OL,13,FMr Brown urged Labour to unite in
OL,14,Ffocusing on putting "the needs of the
OL,15,Fcountry first" in a statement on
OL,16,FMonday evening.
OL,26,@nD@KOUsD@ZO]vD@UOUwD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,F"Whatever the parliamentary games at
OL,7,FWestminster, what the country expects
OL,8,Fof everyone in Labour is to focus on
OL,9,Fthe priorities of the British people,
OL,10,Fwhich is what Keir Starmer is doing
OL,11,Fand for which he deserves all our
OL,12,Fsupport," he said.
OL,14,FDowning Street has said the Government
OL,15,Fis already committing to two
OL,16,Fparliamentary processes ` questioning
OL,17,Ffrom the Foreign Affairs Committee
OL,18,Fabout Lord Mandelson's vetting and a
OL,19,FCommons motion forcing the publication
OL,20,Fof documents relating to his
OL,21,Fappointment.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30214
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,FLord Mandelson's ambassadorship ended
OL,7,Fafter nine months last September when
OL,8,Fhe was sacked over the extent of his
OL,9,Flinks to paedophile financier Jeffrey
OL,10,FEpstein.
OL,12,FOn Tuesday, the Foreign Affairs
OL,13,FCommittee is also due to hear from Sir
OL,14,FKeir's former chief of staff Morgan
OL,15,FMcSweeney, who is widely seen as a
OL,16,Fprotege of Lord Mandelson and resigned
OL,17,Fin February over his part in the
OL,18,Fappointment.
OL,20,FThe committee will also hear from Sir
OL,21,FOlly's predecessor, Sir Philip Barton.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30215
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,FSir Olly, who was sacked by Sir Keir
OL,7,Ffor not disclosing the security
OL,8,Fconcerns to ministers, gave evidence
OL,9,Fto the cross-party group of MPs last
OL,10,Fweek.
OL,12,FSir Olly said he was told the security
OL,13,Fexperts who carried out the vetting
OL,14,Fdeemed Lord Mandelson a "borderline"
OL,15,Fcase and leaned towards recommending
OL,16,Fthat clearance be denied, but the
OL,17,Fofficial approved his developed
OL,18,Fvetting status with mitigations put in
OL,19,Fplace.
OL,26,@vD@YOUvD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30216
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,FDowning Street has said the findings
OL,7,Ffrom UKSV were more clear-cut,
OL,8,Fdescribing Lord Mandelson as of "high
OL,9,Fconcern" and recommending that he be
OL,10,Fdenied clearance.
OL,12,FSir Keir said on Monday he had been
OL,13,Fencouraged by his wife, Lady Victoria
OL,14,FStarmer, to carry on despite months of
OL,15,Fpolitical turbulence and questions
OL,16,Fover the future of his leadership.
OL,18,F"We've got huge amounts of
OL,19,Ftransparency going on already," he
OL,20,Ftold The Cathy Newman Show on Sky News.
OL,26,@pD@aOUqD@HO]zD@AOU{D@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30217
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777345462
OL,3,CStarmer faces crunch vote on Mandelson
OL,4,Cvetting row
OL,6,F"And, frankly, as Prime Minister and
OL,7,Fas a Government, it is really
OL,8,Fimportant I focus on what matters to
OL,9,Fmillions of people across the country."
OL,11,FHe insisted he would keep going for
OL,12,Fthe full five years in office, adding:
OL,13,F"I will be judged at the next election
OL,14,Fon the promises I've made, and I
OL,15,Fintend to deliver on them."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@gO]uD@AOUwD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/17
